            <h3>INFORMATION ABOUT THE ATTRIBUTE RELEASE TO FEDERATED RESOURCES:</h3>
            <p>The {{ idp_metadata['en']['mdui_displayName'] }} with this Identity Provider can send to the requested resource some informations (called attributes) about you.<br/>
            These informations are:</p>
            <ul>
               <li>Needed to access on the resource requested</li>
               <li>Limited to only those informations strictly needed</li>
               <li>Treated by following the law</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The information set sent could change from resource to resource.<br/><br/>
            This Identity Provider will send, to each resource, <strong>only</strong> attributes needed to the access on them.<br/><br/>
            Before the access on the resource, you will view which attributes will be sent where you could decide if consent (or not) the release of such informations.
            If you denied the releasing of the needed attributes, you could not access to the resource requested.<br/><br>
            The following table contains all attributes that your IdP can send to the resources, but only a subset of these attributes will be sent to the resources, the required ones:</p>
            <br />

            <table class="table table-bordered table-responsive" width="70%">
              <tr>
                <th class="col-md-4">Attribute Name</th>
                <th class="col-md-4">Meaning</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>sn</code></td>
                <td>Surname</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>givenName</code></td>
                <td>Name</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
